<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[UAE oil company executives working with Cop28 team, leak reveals]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/22/uae-oil-company-executives-working-with-cop28-team-leak-reveals]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T15:00:02Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/28aa03482d53cfce7e317100405e3fea9f7ce224/0_90_3408_2045 /master/3408.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ea32ea5570ab488d0838daf7d082c1f2&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Cop28 主席 Sultan Al Jaber 本周在纽约举行的一次活动。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;泄露的内部记录显示，阿联酋国家石油公司的高级管理人员正在与 Cop28 团队合作，因为该国在今年晚些时候举行的联合国气候峰会之前加大了公关活动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;两名来自阿联酋国家石油公司的公关专业人士根据气候报告中心 (CCR) 和《卫报》获得的 Cop28 沟通战略文件，阿布扎比国家石油公司 (Adnoc) 被确定为峰会团队提供“额外支持”。这进一步证明了阿联酋 Cop28 团队与其化石燃料行业之间的界限变得模糊。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一月份，Adnoc 首席执行官兼阿联酋气候变化特使 Sultan Al Jaber 被任命为阿布扎比国家石油公司首席执行官。作为第 28 次缔约方会议主席，该会议将于 11 月和 12 月在迪拜举行。从那时起，多份报道引发了人们对他的两个团队之间关系的担忧。 Cop28 团队此前表示，“有明确的治理准则，以确保团队能够完全独立于任何其他实体运作”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Adnoc 工作人员为 Cop28 做公关是完全不合适的， “欧洲企业观察站的研究员帕斯科·萨比多（Pascoe Sabido）说道，他负责协调踢出大污染者联盟。他表示，调查结果清楚地表明了石油公司与峰会团队之间的密切联系。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年早些时候，CCR 和《卫报》透露，Adnoc 的几名工作人员&lt;a href=&quot;https://www .theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/03/uae-oil-company-cop28&quot;>;在峰会上扮演了重要角色&lt;/a>;，包括作为气候谈判代表。有些人甚至是从该石油公司的现有职位中借调的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;6 月，《卫报》报道称，Adnoc 和 Cop28 共享 IT 系统，并且 Adnoc 员工 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian .com/environment/2023/jun/07/uae-oil-firm-cop28-climate-summit-emails-sultan-al-jaber-adnoc&quot;>;能够阅读 Cop28 团队发送和接收的电子邮件&lt;/a>; 。国家石油公司还就如何回应媒体有关此次峰会的询问进行了咨询。当时，Cop28 团队坚称这些电子邮件保存在“独立的、受防火墙保护的网络”上。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;泄露文件中点名的两名 Adnoc 通信高管——菲利普·罗宾逊 (Philip Robinson) 和帕洛玛·贝伦格尔 (Paloma Berenguer)——拥有根据他们的 LinkedIn 账户，他们在化石燃料行业拥有 28 年的经验。在加入阿布扎比国家石油公司之前，他们都曾在壳牌工作过。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Cop28 发言人表示，这两位高管本周没有随团队前往纽约参加联合国大会，也没有参与通讯活动&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“COop28 团队定期收到与 Cop28 无关的询问，并将其转给适当的阿联酋实体来回答，”发言人继续说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该文件列出了 Cop28 团队的职责为出席联合国大会的 Al Jaber 和高级团队成员制定公共关系策略和关键谈话要点。文件指出，联合国会议将“在第二十八届缔约方会议之前定下基调，为气候议程提供信息并塑造气候叙事”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔贾比尔周三在联合国发表讲话时重申， “逐步减少”化石燃料是不可避免且必要的。但他没有呼吁完全逐步淘汰，联合国秘书长安东尼奥·古特雷斯表示，这是缓解全球变暖所必需的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“行动严重不足，”古特雷斯说。 “为了有机会限制全球气温上升，我们必须以公平和公正的方式逐步淘汰石油、煤炭和天然气。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;泄露的通讯计划没有提及逐步减少或分阶段进行。 - 不再使用化石燃料。相反，它的重点是通过提高全球可再生能源产能、减少污染行业的排放以及为绿色投资提供融资来“快速推进能源转型”。作为 Adnoc 首席执行官，Al Jaber 负责监督该公司石油和天然气生产的重大扩张。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“第 28 届缔约方会议主席一贯表示，逐步减少化石燃料是不可避免的，作为Cop28发言人表示：“公平有序的能源转型，必须与快速逐步推广零碳替代品齐头并进。” “这一立场在联合国得到了重申。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿布扎比国家石油公司没有回应置评请求。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;萨比多表示：“化石燃料行业一直在不断地反复推动反对有管理地逐步淘汰所有化石燃料，因为这意味着他们核心业务的终结。”他呼吁采取措施保护联合国免受化石燃料工业和其他石油生产国“普遍”的影响。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Al Jaber 和 Adnoc 都是其中的一部分。但我们不要假装这只是 Al Jaber 一个人。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 23:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Senator Bob Menendez’s home had $480,000 in hidden cash, prosecutors say after federal charges revealed– live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2023/sep/22/government-shutdown-spending-bill-republicans-mccarthy-biden-trump-live-updates]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T15:44:06Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5c89ade5c5c1e5a870077837ff650f9dc43a56a6/0_184_3954_2372 /master/3954.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c8927b8e638cb45f8ed80970bccdc450&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一件印有参议员梅南德斯名字的夹克以及在参议员家中发现的信封中的现金。&lt;/div>;&lt;br>; &lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a >; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 23:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Jellyfish show how you don’t need a brain to learn, say researchers]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/sep/22/jellyfish-learning-behaviour-neurons-study]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T15:00:02Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/02bb011fc22bc9f7ba6b715985b8deac0727bdc2/0_0_2401_1659 /master/2401.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=e62b742b49ac3ef940a9fb06113ed6de&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;加勒比箱水母&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;研究人员透露，水母会根据过去的经验改变其行为，一项研究表明学习可能是神经细胞工作方式的基本属性。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与人类不同，水母没有中枢大脑。然而，箱形水母具有与该生物的眼状结构（称为rhopalia）相关的神经元簇，该系统充当视觉信息处理中心。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;现在，研究小型加勒比箱形水母的研究人员表示，他们我们发现这些生物能够通过一种称为联想学习的过程从过去的经验中学习，就像巴甫洛夫的狗学习&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/gallery/2014/jun/23/animals&quot; >;听到铃声就会流口水&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们补充说，到目前为止，这种能力只有更复杂的动物（例如脊椎动物和软体动物）才明确显示出来。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;研究人员表示，鉴于学习能力对于生存至关重要，他们的结果并不令人意外。但是，由于水母属于最早进化的动物群体之一，他们表示，研究结果表明这种学习可能是神经细胞的一个不可或缺的功能。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你不需要高度发达的大脑来学习;基尔大学这项研究的第一作者 Jan Bielecki 博士说：“它是神经细胞本身不可或缺的一部分。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cell.com/current-biology /fulltext/S0960-9822(23)01136-3&quot;>;Bielecki 和同事在《当代生物学》杂志上撰文&lt;/a>;，报告了他们如何通过记录加勒比箱形水母被放入水箱时的行为来获得这一发现装饰有不同的图案。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;12只水母被放入灰白条纹墙壁的水箱中，7只被放入黑白条纹水箱中，8只被放入纯灰色墙壁的水箱中。研究小组表示，条纹墙模仿了红树林根部，水母在自然栖息地会试图躲避红树林根部，以避免对其脆弱的身体造成伤害。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;研究人员发现，水母被放置在黑白条纹水箱中从未与侧面发生碰撞 - 可能是因为条纹代表附近的障碍物 - 但普通灰色水箱中的水母经常撞到墙壁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，虽然灰色条纹水箱中的水母最初与墙壁发生碰撞，这种行为在 7.5 分钟内减少，动物与墙壁的距离增加了约 50%，每分钟与墙壁的接触次数减少了一半。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;研究小组表示，这表明，虽然水母最初将灰色条纹视为远处的障碍物，他们很快了解到这种图案与碰撞风险增加有关。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在一组实验中，研究人员解剖了加勒比箱形水母，以分离出水母和相关神经元.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;当研究小组向这些结构呈现移动的灰色条纹时，他们在神经元中没有检测到任何反应。但在将移动条纹与电击配对以模拟碰撞后，研究小组发现系统随后单独对移动条纹做出反应，发送信号，导致活体动物突然游泳——换句话说，发出信号可以让水母躲避障碍物。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;研究小组表示，研究结果表明学习中心位于rhopalia，并且学习是基于视觉和机械刺激的结合。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;但 Bielecki 补充说，他们还指出了另一个结论：“它支持了这一建议，即很少，甚至可能只有一个神经细胞能够学习，”他说。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 23:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[US senator Robert Menendez and wife charged with bribery offenses]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/22/robert-menendez-wife-bribery-charges]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T14:04:52Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/974b7bb53aae8e9906ecd7c4de34e1d4c2a3fe39/0_13_3000_1799 /master/3000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fd89b0f9f1a8f71fa8d9b3c3d1ed3f1c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;罗伯特·梅嫩德斯。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;美国新泽西州民主党参议员罗伯特·梅嫩德斯和他的联邦检察官周五表示，妻子因与三名新泽西州商人的关系而被指控犯有贿赂罪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;曼哈顿美国检察官办公室指控被告收受数千美元的贿赂，以换取利用梅嫩德斯作为参议员的权力和影响力，寻求保护商人并使其致富，并使埃及政府受益。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;检察官称，贿赂包括现金、黄金、住房抵押贷款、工作补偿最低限度的要求，一辆豪华汽车和其他有价值的东西。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;梅南德斯和他的妻子每人面临三项刑事指控。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;梅南德斯是美国参议院外交关系委员会主席，此前曾在新泽西州被指控接受富有赞助人的私人航班、竞选捐款和其他贿赂以换取官方恩惠，但 2017 年的审判以陪审团陷入僵局而告终。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;联邦政府现在寻求没收的资产包括 Mendezes 新泽西州的住宅、一辆 2019 年款梅赛德斯-奔驰汽车、约 566,000 美元的现金、金条和银行账户资金。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 22:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Tom Ford’s British creative director makes debut at Milan fashion week]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/sep/22/tom-ford-british-creative-director-makes-debut-at-milan-fashion-week]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T11:49:33Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/03858c77ec20de121105628fed8272ac2629361b/0_188_5639_3383 /master/5639.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c432146676e9fe39c949ec85da732f64&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;2023 年 9 月 21 日米兰时装周 2024 年春夏女装时装周期间，模特们在 Tom Ford 时装秀上走秀米兰&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;&lt;br>; 汤姆·福特 (Tom Ford) 的造型——一种为享乐主义者打造的时髦、光鲜亮丽的 90 年代风格极简主义——今年又重新流行起来，就在福特本人离开的时候。福特去年以 28 亿美元的价格将其公司出售给雅诗兰黛，并放弃了设计职责。但在米兰时装周上，他的长期门生、英国设计师彼得·霍金斯 (Peter Hawkings) 推出的首个系列，为汤姆·福特 (Tom Ford) 时尚在没有汤姆·福特 (Tom Ford) 本人的情况下也能保持活力提供了令人信服的别致案例。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位魅力超凡的主唱缺席了。 ，但最伟大的歌曲都被完美地演唱了。最紧身的天鹅绒裤装与其说是剪裁，不如说是剪裁得恰到好处。丝绸衬衫的扣子解开到肚脐。晚装凉鞋的针跟摇摇欲坠。其中有闪亮的仿鳄鱼皮外套、狩猎夹克、紧身连衣裙臀部挂着的雕塑般的皮带扣。在晚上 9.30 的昏暗灯光秀场上，每位模特都戴着墨镜。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;5c5a6e4d563ceeeec963c61fc2b817a01610f5df&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/5c5a6e4d563ceeeec963c61fc2b817a01610f5 df/ 0_0_4001_6000/667.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;男模特穿着 Tom Ford 天鹅绒长裤、丝绸衬衫和亮片夹克。&quot; width=&quot;667&quot; height=&quot;1000&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;解扣丝绸衬衫和剪裁紧身的裤子，与熟悉的 Tom Ford 造型一脉相承。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Justin Shin/Getty Images&lt;/span >; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;霍金斯版本的汤姆·福特与原版的不同之处在于它更加谦虚。 Ford 是一位挑衅者，他在 1997 年春夏时装秀上让一位模特穿着开放式针织毛衣走上 T 台，化着浓浓的烟熏眼妆，但下半身什么都没有，除了一条 G 字带，上面有互扣的 G 标志。臀部。霍金斯似乎并不认同这种半裸时装秀的品味。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;演出结束后在后台，当被问及他心目中的汤姆·福特 (Tom Ford) 女人是谁时，霍金斯立即指定了他的妻子、企业家惠特尼·布罗姆伯格·霍金斯 (Whitney Bromberg Hawkings)。这对夫妇是在福特公司工作时认识的，之后布罗姆伯格·霍金斯离开并成立了在线花卉公司 Flowerbx。 “我的妻子是汤姆·福特的女人。我很幸运有一个坚强的妻子，她有强烈的意见，她准确地告诉我什么有效，什么无效。”霍金斯说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;4505c11cdc4c6379ed497b07c7b844e8388060cc&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https: //media.guim.co.uk/4505c11cdc4c6379ed497b07c7b844e8388060cc/0_0_4000_6000/667.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;穿着粉色西装的模特。&quot; width=&quot;667&quot; height=&quot;1000&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;霍金的设计中没有与汤姆·福特相关的半裸时装秀。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Justin Shin/Getty Images&lt;/span >; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;这些衣服的优雅气质反映出设计师听取了职业女性的反馈。 20 世纪 90 年代看起来颓废而令人兴奋的审美观对于现代品味来说可能有点低俗，所以这感觉像是一种当代的更新。然而，这可能会让衣服缺乏令人兴奋的感觉，福特比任何人都清楚，这对于让一个品牌保持在聚光灯下至关重要。雅诗兰黛收购汤姆福特主要是为了一家美容公司——汤姆福特香水和化妆品拥有忠实的粉丝群，他们支付更高的价格——这意味着汤姆福特作为服装系列的未来仍然悬而未决。&lt;/p>; &lt;图data-media-id=&quot;ce445fa0af1141ad9f6c3bb21906a26df12c7e3e&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/ce445fa0af1141ad9f6c3bb21906a26df12c7e3e/0_0_4000_6000/667.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;模特穿着蓝色紧身连衣裙。” width=&quot;667&quot; height=&quot;1000&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;紧身连衣裙和凉鞋是模特无处不在的太阳镜下面的常见搭配。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Justin Shin/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt; /figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;福特原计划在前排支持霍金斯，但恶劣天气造成的航班中断使他无法前往米兰。暴雨也打乱了新设计师 Sabato de Sarno 首次亮相 Gucci 的计划。 Gucci 原计划在米兰布雷拉学院周围的街道上举办一场露天秀，设想在市中心举办一场活动，居民们可以在自家的阳台上观看——这是一个寻求回归之路的品牌对米兰传统的象征性复兴。在经历了亚历山德罗·米歇尔 (Alessandro Michele) 的极端古怪时代后，他终于踏上了坚实的基础。上午 11 点，周五的秀场移至 Gucci 现代主义总部的室内场地。 Gucci 发言人表示：“做出这一决定的首要任务是确保所有生产工人的安全，并为客人提供尽可能最佳的体验。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href= “https://feedx.best” style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 20:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Italian MP calls for museum director to be sacked for being ‘racist towards Italians’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/italian-mp-calls-for-museum-director-to-be-sacked-for-being-racist-towards-italians]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T11:45:59Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/a03329783e7d7c2ec1ae78dc44df6f04728b5d1c/0_195_4748_2850 /master/4748.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=206d5340e51f2612fdfa2468674d3c71&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;都灵埃及博物馆&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;一位意大利政客正在力推一家著名博物馆的馆长被“踢出”，认为他“对意大利人有种族主义”，此举引发了人们对乔治亚·梅洛尼极右翼政府明显试图加强对文化的控制的争论。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;梅洛尼执政联盟成员、联盟副领导人安德里亚·克里帕 (Andrea Crippa) 表示，自 2014 年以来一直管理北部城市都灵埃及博物馆的克里斯蒂安·格雷科 (Christian Greco) 是一名“左翼馆长”，他以“意识形态”的方式管理博物馆。克里帕的抱怨可以追溯到 2018 年 2 月，当时格雷科向讲阿拉伯语的人提供折扣门票，以表彰博物馆来自埃及的文物，并作为促进阿拉伯国家之间对话的一种方式。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但这一举措在欧洲最成功的博物馆之一的博物馆外引发了极右翼的抗议，其中包括梅洛尼，他的意大利兄弟党当时的支持率还不到 4%。梅洛尼形容这个想法是“愚蠢的”和“对意大利人的歧视”。去年十月上台之前，她长期以来一直反对“伊斯兰化”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利兄弟会皮埃蒙特地区福利委员毛里齐奥·马罗内 (Maurizio Marrone) 本周在都灵版《晚邮报》上发表讲话后，这个问题再次出现。格列柯的任期可能不会延长，因为他认为有“更合格的人物”。皮埃蒙特的领导权在去年的地区选举中落入右翼联盟手中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;克里帕的反应也是在他在格雷科因涉嫌煽动仇恨而提起的法律诉讼中被洗清之后做出的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >;他告诉意大利媒体，格雷科应该“做出有尊严的举动并辞职”。 “我们将尽一切努力把他赶出去，如果他不辞职，我们要求文化部长[Gennaro] Sangiuliano解雇他，”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在格雷科的领导下，博物馆的门票销售旅游业蓬勃发展，到 2022 年，该网站的游客人数将超过 90 万，比大流行前的水平增加了 6.3%，而且外面一直在排队。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在周四接受《La Stampa》采访时，意大利人格雷科 (Greco)曾在国外工作过的他为自己的记录进行了辩护，称“政治干预只存在于意大利”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“在意大利，政治干预过度，破坏了平衡，是一个一直存在的问题，”他添加。 “在国外工作的七年里，我从未见过政治家。”桑朱利亚诺过去曾暗示政府将限制雇用外国博物馆馆长，但他没有对这一事件做出回应。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;文化部副部长维托里奥·斯加尔比 (Vittorio Sgarbi) 在 8 月份表示，一些高级职位应该留给意大利人，政府在招聘过程中引入了新标准，例如对申请人的要求更加严格。语言技能。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;几位反对党政客为格雷科辩护，其中包括前文化部长达里奥·弗朗西斯基尼。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“文化是一个不应卷入政治冲突的领域，”他说。 “认为执政者应该只任命效忠者是错误的，而且可能会自食其果。”来自中左翼民主党的劳拉·博德里尼 (Laura Boldrini) 表示，克里帕的话是“独裁和专有思想”的表达，描述这种做法“对国家和民主来说都是令人不安的”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;来自小型中间派政党 Azione 的丹妮拉·鲁菲诺 (Daniela Ruffino) 表示：“寻求利用享有盛誉和受人尊敬的埃及古物学家克里斯蒂安·格列柯 (Christian Greco) 来进行研究。针对伊斯兰教的宗教战争充分说明了政治斗争的程度。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net “ style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target= &quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 20:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Marine Le Pen should stand trial over alleged misuse of EU funds, say prosecutors]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/marine-le-pen-trial-alleged-misuse-eu-funds-say-prosecutors]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T11:35:43Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c8bbe42ce87317dd9e2becb413432757f9f672a2/0_15_6000_3600 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=bd8fff02858f9d03f1fad62bfbbc0c3c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;玛丽娜·勒庞&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;巴黎检察官办公室建议极右翼领导人玛丽娜·勒庞Pen 和她的&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jan/11/france-far-right-le-pen-2027-sanitise-image&quot;>;全国集会&lt;/该党因涉嫌滥用欧盟资金而接受审判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该请求将由法官考虑，该请求是在对该党（当时称为国民阵线）的指控进行了七年调查之后提出的。使用原本用于欧盟议会助理的资金来支付 2004 年至 2016 年间为该党工作的工作人员的工资。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟立法者获得拨款用于支付费用，包括其助理的费用，但无意将其用于&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;此案涉及 11 名欧洲议会议员，包括勒庞和她 95 岁的父亲、前党魁让-马里·勒庞，以及 13 名议会助理。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;勒庞是法国议会议员，她的极右翼政党是法国最大的单一反对党。她正准备在 2027 年第四次竞选总统，届时埃马纽埃尔·马克龙将没有资格再次竞选。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;全国集会否认有不当行为。该党在一份声明中告诉路透社：“我们对这一立场提出异议，这似乎是对反对派议员及其助手工作的错误理解，这首先是政治工作。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;勒庞此前曾表示否认有不当行为。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在审判中，勒庞可能面临 10 年监禁和 100 万欧元（87 万英镑）罚款，并且由于她是民选官员，10 年内不得担任公职年，检察官办公室表示。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target= &quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.最好&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 19:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Armenian PM hopes ethnic Armenians can remain in Nagorno-Karabakh]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/armenian-pm-hopes-ethnic-armenians-can-remain-in-nagorno-karabakh-azerbaijan]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T11:22:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/9500342b71c64f636c9dd1bb646501532037af57/0_0_3600_2160 /master/3600.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=a0b2c3e339a1e3da7466d19235844b6a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;斯捷潘纳克特附近营地的平民&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;亚美尼亚总理 Nikol Pashinyan 表示希望亚美尼亚人可以留在纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫，因为担心阿塞拜疆正在寻求驱逐数万人。阿塞拜疆声称在本周发动军事进攻后控制了该地区。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在埃里温举行的政府会议上发表讲话帕希尼扬表示，亚美尼亚将欢迎居住在分离地区的亚美尼亚人，但只有当卡拉巴赫亚美尼亚人无法留在那里时，才会进行大规模重新安置。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;大约有 12 万亚美尼亚人居住在南高加索飞地，该飞地是卡拉巴赫地区的亚美尼亚人。国际上承认阿塞拜疆的一部分，但自 1994 年以来一直处于亚美尼亚族的控制之下。军事进攻。双方周四举行了第一轮会谈，讨论该地区及其居民的未来。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿塞拜疆一名高级官员周五表示，巴库将确保平民能够安全地乘坐自己的车辆沿着巴库旅行。从纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫穿过拉钦走廊通往亚美尼亚的道路。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-interactive=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/embed/iframe-wrapper/0.1/boot.js&quot; data- canonical-url=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/09/archive-zip/giv-134250YMUrnB4SvNC/&quot; data-alt=&quot;纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫地图&quot;>; &lt;a href=&quot; https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/09/archive-zip/giv-134250YMUrnB4SvNC/&quot;>;互动&lt;/a>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Hikmet Hajiyev，外交政策顾问阿塞拜疆总统还表示，阿塞拜疆将保证赦免放弃武器的卡拉巴赫亚美尼亚战士，尽管他声称一些卡拉巴赫军事单位已表示将继续抵抗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;与此同时，一名卡拉巴赫代表告诉法国通讯社-新闻社称，阿塞拜疆军队在该地区首府斯捷潘纳克特（阿塞拜疆称为汉肯迪）边缘，促使居民惊恐地躲在地下室。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“斯捷潘纳克特的情况非常可怕，阿塞拜疆军队遍布整个城市，他们在郊区，人们担心阿塞拜疆士兵可能随时进入城市并开始杀戮，”分离主义发言人阿尔米恩·海拉佩蒂安 (Armine Hayrapetyan) 说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;帕希尼扬 (Pashinyan) 周四晚强调。分离地区的停火已基本实现。但其他亚美尼亚官员表示，阿塞拜疆正在为该地区的“种族清洗”做准备。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;亚美尼亚外交部长阿拉拉特·米尔佐扬 (Ararat Mirzoyan) 在联合国安理会会议上发言时表示：“这次攻势清楚地表明，其目的是完成对纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫亚美尼亚人的种族清洗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡拉巴赫的人道主义局势不断恶化也发出了警告。卡拉巴赫的人权监察员格格姆·斯捷潘尼扬 (Gegham Stepanyan) 在社交媒体上表示，斯捷潘纳克特的街道“挤满了流离失所的人，他们饥饿、恐惧、充满不确定性”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“人们拼命地寻找彼此。” &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;观察家表示，阿塞拜疆去年春天封锁拉钦走廊，切断了亚美尼亚和纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫之间的人员和货物流动，之后卡拉巴赫的许多人已经被削弱了。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周五，纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫的亚美尼亚族领导人表示，已就来自亚美尼亚的人道主义车队达成协议。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/20/nagorno-karabakh-events-show- Russia-grip-on-its-old-backyard-is-slipping-azerbaijan-armenia&quot;>;纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫事件表明俄罗斯对其老后院的控制正在减弱&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;有未经证实的报道称阿塞拜疆军队袭击了平民。纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫的一名分离主义官员表示，阿塞拜疆发动攻势后，已造成至少 200 人死亡、400 多人受伤，其中包括至少 10 名平民和 5 名儿童。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Siranush Sargsyan，纳戈尔诺自由撰稿人-卡拉巴赫，在网上分享的视频显示，斯捷潘纳克特 Azatamartikneri 大道上的民用车辆被毁，公寓楼受损。&lt;br>;&lt;br>;自 1994 年分离主义战争结束以来，纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫及周边大片领土一直处于亚美尼亚族人的控制之下，但阿塞拜疆在2020年的战斗中收复了纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫的领土和部分地区。最终停战协议将俄罗斯维和部队部署在纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周四，阿塞拜疆总统伊尔哈姆·阿利耶夫在与弗拉基米尔·普京的电话中就六名俄罗斯维和部队在阿塞拜疆炮火中丧生一事道歉。从纳戈尔诺-卡拉巴赫巡逻返回时。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 19:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Migration could be ‘dissolving force for EU’, says bloc’s top diplomat]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/migration-eu-diplomat-josep-borrell-ukraine-china]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T11:39:11Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/00cbd6bfa1708cc4f0d295b9ef40159b7419c3aa/0_0_7661_4597 /master/7661.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b09cf48ed4c1b19fd848d93e0ac2141d&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;本月早些时候在比利时的 Josep Borrell。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;移民可能是“一股溶解力量”欧盟最高外交官表示，由于欧洲国家之间深厚的文化差异以及长期无法达成共同政策，“欧盟”的立场越来越强。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管俄罗斯将试图在欧洲内部煽动移民问题何塞普·博雷尔否认乌克兰战争本身加剧了这场危机，他称这是一个数十年之久的问题，由出发国的战争和贫困加剧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;欧盟外交事务专员表示，欧盟已经在战争中创造了奇迹，并且它是建立新世界秩序的关键力量之一，在这个新秩序中，全球南方应该得到更大的尊重和权力。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在接受《卫报》的广泛采访时反思了如何他表示，欧盟已经因战争而发生了变化，欧盟也适应了新的世界秩序，欧洲国家被迫从国防开支的午睡中醒来，他们一直生活在美国的核保护伞下。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;2ad145c0ee1871e2c0022152d86a7a43732cb053&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/2ad145c0ee1871e2c0022152d86a7a43732cb053/0_401_6000_3599/10 00.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;何塞普·博雷尔在联合国安理会紧急会议上发言讨论亚美尼亚和阿塞拜疆之间的局势。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;约瑟夫·博雷尔 (Josep Borrell) 在最近一次联合国安理会紧急会议上发言，讨论亚美尼亚和阿塞拜疆之间的局势。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Michael M Santiago/盖蒂图片社&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;他呼吁加强防务合作，更快地就向乌克兰供应武器做出决定，并为步履蹒跚的反攻辩护，称该国三分之一的地区布有地雷，对于乌克兰发动全面正面反击，无异于自杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他随后在纽约大学法学院的一次演讲中表示，事实证明，联合国安理会近年来“毫无用处，因为其分歧”，并呼吁对政治和金融机构进行改革，以重振“已经过时且失去动力”的多边主义。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;最近几天&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian. com/world/2023/sep/20/giorgia-meloni-i-wont-allow-italy-to-become-europe-refugee-camp&quot;>;意大利极右翼总理乔治亚·梅洛尼&lt;/a>;，他来到power on the back of controversial rhetoric about the rise of migration, said that she would not allow her country to become “Europe&#39;s refugee camp” after 11,000 people arrived on the island of Lampedusa in a matter of days.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; Borrell said nationalism was on the rise in Europe but said this was more about migration than Euroscepticism. “Brexit actually was feared to be an epidemic. And it has not been,” he said. “It has been a vaccine. No one wants to follow the British leaving the European Union.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Migration is a bigger divide for the European Union. And it could be a dissolving force for the European Union.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Despite establishing a shared common external border, “we have not been able until now to agree on a common migration policy”, he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He attributed this to deep cultural and political differences inside the EU: “There are some members of the European Union that are Japanese-style – we don&#39;t want to mix. We don&#39;t want migrants. We don&#39;t want to accept people from outside. We want our purity.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said other countries, such as Spain, have a long history of accepting migrants. “The paradox is that Europe needs migrants because we have so low demographic growth. If we want to survive from a labour point of view, we need migrants.”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;c6975d55ba8a605c281b0b409c34963a45aefce9&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/c6975d55ba8a605c281b0b409c34963a45aefce9/0_402_6017_3609/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Migrants arrive in the harbour of Italian island of Lampedusa, on 18 September 2023.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Migrants arrive in the harbour of Italian island of Lampedusa, on 18 September 2023.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Zakaria Abdelkafi/AFP/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Borrell insisted in the interview that the war in Ukraine was not fuelling the current rows over migration. “The issue is that migration pressure has been increasing, mainly due to wars – not the war against Ukraine … It is the Syrian war, the Libyan war, the military coups in Sahel.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We are living in a circle of instability from Gibraltar to the Caucasus and this happened before the Ukrainian war and will continue after the Ukrainian war. Migration in Africa is not being caused by the war against Ukraine. The root causes of migration in Africa are lack of development, economic growth and bad governance.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said European efforts to cooperate with some African countries had been made more difficult by the existence of military regimes. He described the Wagner group, the Russian mercenary outfit, as “the praetorian guard of the African dictators”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Asked if he believed Russia would try to fan the flames of migration, he said “Putin will try everything”. He added: “Putin believes that democracies are weak, fragile, they get tired and time is running on his side, because sooner or later, we will get exhausted. And this is a political battle as much as a military battle. It has to be explained with arguments. Certainly nobody likes to pay more for the electricity bills. I believe in democracy as a pedagogical exercise, and I believe that people understand the reasons.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But he also acknowledged the harsh choices Europe faced in curbing migration by reaching deals with countries such as Tunisia, pointing out it is his duty to defend not just European values but at the same time European interests. “The life of the diplomat is full of uncomfortable choices … Foreign policy is working for the values and the interests of the European Union. And these require, in some cases, difficult choices trying all the time to respect international law and human rights.”&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;&lt;strong>;Ukraine and the EU&lt;/strong>;&lt;/h2>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;639d4d2305f149b1cc0485ae1deadf97e1f62304&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/639d4d2305f149b1cc0485ae1deadf97e1f62304/0_389_5820_3491/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Flags of Ukraine and EU rise in front of the Nato emblem in central Kyiv, 11 July 2023.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Flags of Ukraine and EU rise in front of the Nato emblem in central Kyiv, 11 July 2023.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Valentyn Ogirenko/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Increasingly a target for personal criticism by the Russian foreign minister, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/10/russian-minister-says-g20-summit-a-success-after-criticism-over-war-blocked&quot;>;Sergei Lavrov&lt;/a>;, Borrell was at the heart of the decision to persuade EU states to supply arms to Kyiv as Russian troops crossed the border – indeed he says it is the proudest moment of his career.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The former Spanish foreign minister cuts an unusual figure, since he seems as much a geopolitical commentator as a practitioner. He insists the public mood in Europe is not fracturing on Ukraine.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Asked if the disputes between some eastern European countries and Ukraine over grain exports are a harbinger of the conflicts that might arise if the country joins the EU, he said: “Everybody knows, it&#39;s going to be difficult, because Ukraine, first of all, is at war and is being destroyed, literally. Second, it had to do a lot of reforms even before the war. And third, at this moment Ukraine being a member of the European Union it would be the only country that would be a net beneficiary.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As a result both Ukraine and the EU will need to undertake a long reform process, including in his mind greater use of majority voting.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Either way, he said, Ukraine&#39;s membership means the end of what he described as a “sleeping siesta” about EU enlargement. “For years and years there has been a kind of stalemate and nothing happened. Ukraine has created a new dynamic.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We are herbivores in a world of carnivores. It is a power politics world, yet we still have in mind that through trade and preaching the rule of law we can have influence on the world. We must still preach the rule of law, but we have to be aware there are some leaders that need to be dealt with in a different way.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said the EU was still a long way from having the defence capacity it needed.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I am not Donald Trump saying you have to spend 2% of GDP on defence, but it is in our hands to build a common foreign and defence policy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The war, he said, “had required a live exercise working out the capacities Europe has, what it can provide, what Ukraine can use, where there are duplications, where there are the loopholes”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said the EU had achieved miracles and acted at the speed of light in comparison with the past.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But he added: “Some decisions have been discussed for quite a long time. Do we have to provide tanks? This has been a long discussion, and at the end, we provide tanks. Do we have to provide Patriot anti-aircraft missiles? There has been a long discussion and at the end we did it. Do we have to provide air force capacities? This was discussed just at the beginning of the war. Now we are training pilots for the F 16. Certainly, a war is a war, and if you want to supply arms to someone who is at war and is receiving heavy attacks, the quicker the better.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Although he thinks quicker decisions might have saved lives, he pointed out that the the progress of the Ukrainian counteroffensive has been slowed by problems beyond arms supplies. “Russia has built a long string of fortifications,” he said. “In some cases 25km deep, or wide. And it&#39;s clear that you cannot launch a frontal attack against that, it would be suicide. They have been mining the whole land.”&lt;/p>; &lt;h2>;&lt;strong>;A new world order?&lt;/strong>;&lt;/h2>; &lt;p>;Borrell predicted that the war in Ukraine, and the eventual outcome of its struggle, would be one of the three driving forces creating a new world order, alongside competition between China and the US, and the rise of the global south.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He admitted he was no fan of the term “global south” to describe such a heterogeneous group of people, but that an entity exists that “consider themselves part of an alternative to the western models”. He said it was critical to “try to avoid the alliance of China plus Russia, plus parts of the global south”.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;89212f5a44bdfff54b8b27d5735abbc99069ed70&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/89212f5a44bdfff54b8b27d5735abbc99069ed70/0_92_2742_1646/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;The president of Brazil, Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva, the president of China, Xi Jinping, South African president, Cyril Ramaphosa, prime minister of India, Narendra Modi, and Russia&#39;s foreign minister, Sergei Lavrov, pose for a photo during the 2023 Brics summit in Johannesburg.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;The president of Brazil, Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva, the president of China, Xi Jinping, South African president, Cyril Ramaphosa, prime minister of India, Narendra Modi, and Russia&#39;s foreign minister, Sergei Lavrov, pose for a photo during the 2023 Brics summit in Johannesburg.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;“The people of the global south want to be recognised because 40, 50 years ago, when the world order was built, some of these countries did not exist. Either they were colonies, or so poor they did not have a vote.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“So now they are independent countries and they have been growing economically, demographically, and they want to have a say.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said “understandably these countries are hedging. One day they look at Russia , another at China. At the UN they vote against the war in Ukraine but many of them do not have this feeling of moral indignation that we have.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“There is no clear hegemon in the world, but instead a growing number of actors in the world.” The paradox, he said, was that this growth in actors has not been accompanied by a stronger multilateralism.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We have multipolarity without multilateralism. I am an engineer by training and I know when there are more poles in the game you need more rules in the game. But we have more poles and less rules and that is why the world is so unstable because the powers are confronting one another, and either they create blockages or a landslide.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Look at all these countries, South Africa, Brazil, Indonesia, India &lt;strong>;–&lt;/strong>; you cannot ignore this new reality. In 20 years, at the current trend, there will be three big countries in the world, China, India and the US. Each of these powers will be a $50tn economy, and the EU will be much less about $30tn.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“For Europe this represents a huge long-term challenge. Europeans have to be prepared to be part of the new world in which we will be a smaller part of the population, certainly, and also in proportion to the size of the world economy. It means that we have to look for political influence, technological capacity and unity. Unity is the key word. Europeans have to be more united.”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 19:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Trial of two Chinese activists held since 2021 begins in secret in Guangzhou]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/trial-of-two-chinese-activists-held-since-2021-begins-in-secret-in-guangzhou]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T09:21:03Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/fd9fd925b36f4eaece6dbfe14de1c2963bc26f5f/0_161_5458_3275/master/5458.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1da9298dade27b176044779b3f23815c&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Huang Xueqin&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The trial of two prominent activists detained since 2021 has begun in secret in the Chinese city of Guangzhou, in a case that has attracted widespread attention to Beijing&#39;s repression of civil society.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/16/journalist-held-without-trial-china-urgent-medical-attention-huang-xueqin&quot;>;Huang Xueqin&lt;/a>;, a feminist activist and journalist who covered China&#39;s #MeToo movement, and Wang Jianbing, a labour rights activist, were detained in Guangzhou in September 2021, shortly before Huang was due to move to the UK to study at the University of Sussex. The pair were charged with “inciting subversion of state power” the following month. The charge normally carries a sentence of up to five years, although terms can be longer in cases deemed severe.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The roads around the courthouses appeared to be closed to public access, supporters said on Friday morning.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The pair have been held largely incommunicado. Advocates say they have been subjected to secret interrogations, torture and ill-treatment. In the weeks after their detention, Guangzhou police interrogated nearly 70 of their acquaintances, according to Chinese Human Rights Defenders (CHRD), a US-based human rights NGO. Several of those people were later forced to leave Guangzhou.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In the year leading up to their arrest, Huang and Wang had organised weekly meetings at Wang&#39;s apartment in Guangzhou for like-minded progressives, to discuss issues such as feminism, LGBTQ+ rights and labour issues, but also to watch films and play board games. A friend of the pair who regularly attended said: “They were trying to rebuild a network, to bring together every isolated individual.” Wang was a “tea addict” and he and Huang would prepare a spread of drinks and snacks for the casual meetings. “We never thought that this was dangerous, or even offensive to the government,” said the friend.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;aa3b722ed1b7a82c1d18b4e633e9ec88884d3161&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/aa3b722ed1b7a82c1d18b4e633e9ec88884d3161/0_167_5000_3000/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Wang Jianbing.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Wang Jianbing.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;As well as China&#39;s #MeToo movement, Huang covered the pro-democracy movement in Hong Kong as a journalist. Reflecting on reporting on the 2019 protests, Huang wrote: “Of course I understand the risks of pursuing freedom, and right now I am paying the price of being away from my loved ones back home.” Huang was later detained in Guangzhou and prevented from taking up a place on a postgraduate programme at the University of Hong Kong.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;After being released in January 2020, Huang gained a certain cachet among activists in Guangzhou, who sometimes saw imprisonment as a badge of honour, said Mako, a friend of Huang&#39;s, who uses a pseudonym to protect her identity. Huang was “appalled” by that attitude. “She didn&#39;t think that she was superior just because she has been detained. Somehow she became even more down to earth, even more humble,” said Mako, who also attended the weekly meetings.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In June 2021, the British Foreign Office awarded Huang a Chevening scholarship, through a scheme which supports “outstanding emerging leaders from all over the world”. Huang was due to start a master&#39;s degree in at the University of Sussex that autumn.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A spokesperson for the university said: “The University of Sussex community remains deeply concerned about Sophia Huang Xueqin, her safety and her wellbeing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We have consistently raised her case in meetings with the UK government and in correspondence with the British embassy in China.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A spokesperson for the Foreign Office said: “We have directly raised our concerns on this case with the Chinese authorities on several occasions. Nobody should be arrested and put on trial for exercising their fundamental rights. British diplomats will seek to attend the trial.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Representatives of seven consulates including the US attempted to attend the trial on Friday, but were not allowed into the courthouse.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;William Nee, a researcher at CHRD, said that the Chinese authorities were often “very reluctant” to let people such as Huang go abroad. “If they&#39;re abroad they can speak freely, they can connect with others and pose a threat to the regime.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Tuesday, Huang and Wang saw each other for what is believed to be the first time since they were detained, at a pre-trial meeting.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/china-global-surge-mpox-world-health-organization&quot;>;China fuels global surge in mpox cases as LGBTQ+ stigma hampers response&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The pair are being held in Guangzhou number one detention centre. The prison did not respond to calls from the Guardian. Guangzhou&#39;s public security bureau could not be reached for comment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Huang was previously reported to be in poor health, having lost a significant amount of weight, although her situation is thought to have improved more recently.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In April 2022, Huang fired the lawyer that her family had appointed to represent her. She signed a letter dismissing Wan Miaoyan, a Chengdu-based lawyer who has known her for several years. In other cases, the Chinese authorities have been known to force detained people to dismiss their chosen counsel. But Wan has since managed to be reappointed. She declined to be interviewed but told the Guardian: “As her lawyer, I will do my best as any lawyer could do.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Thursday, 32 civil society groups, including Amnesty International and Reporters Without Borders, published a joint statement calling for the “immediate and unconditional” release of Huang and Wang.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Additional reporting by Tzu-Wei Liu&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 17:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Tories accuse Starmer of ‘flip-flopping’ over EU following claims Labour wants to undo Brexit – UK politics live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2023/sep/22/brexit-eu-tories-keir-starmer-labour-rishi-sunak-uk-politics-latest]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-22T09:21:08Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/a5778bc3faee52cf3276e1d4a20b498b2d416174/1221_89_1657_995/master/1657.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=4cbab80a8eeeca43f6787010f6d4cbc8&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Keir Starmer.&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 22 Sep 2023 17:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>